snippet.textDisplay: Hi Jeffree, I live in Canada and it gets super cold here. My whole face gets so dry in the winter, lids included. I found that if you replace using make-up wipes with baby wipes to take off your eye make up or your whole face, it is more gentle on your skin and the dryness doesn't flake up as much. After you wash, exfoliate and moisturize, you can try laying a wash cloth that was soaked in boiling water, let it cool down a bit, obviously and then place it over your face, and it will help lock in the moisture that escapes during the day, if its due to weather, stress or even allergies.
snippet.textOriginal: Hi Jeffree, I live in Canada and it gets super cold here. My whole face gets so dry in the winter, lids included. I found that if you replace using make-up wipes with baby wipes to take off your eye make up or your whole face, it is more gentle on your skin and the dryness doesn't flake up as much. After you wash, exfoliate and moisturize, you can try laying a wash cloth that was soaked in boiling water, let it cool down a bit, obviously and then place it over your face, and it will help lock in the moisture that escapes during the day, if its due to weather, stress or even allergies.
